HEADWORD: Solon
<hw>So"lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A celebrated Athenian
lawmaker, born about 638 <sc>b. c.</sc>; hence, a legislator; a
publicist; -- often used ironically.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

